cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is likely because the paper deals with the analysis of transmit powers and beamforming vectors to guarantee target rates in a MIMO system with perfect CSI.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is likely because the paper considers a multi-user MIMO system and studies the energy consumption distribution when different linear precoding techniques are used.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is likely because the paper studies the energy consumption distribution in a MIMO system with mobility and aims to design the cell radius for minimizing the energy consumption per unit area.
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is likely because the paper considers multiple single-antenna user equipments (UEs) that move around in the cell according to a random walk mobility model.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible because the paper deals with the downlink of a MIMO system that communicates with single-antenna UEs.
